# User-defined stopwords example file for GoldenDict-NG
# 
# To use this file:
# 1. Copy this file to your GoldenDict configuration directory
# 2. Rename it to "stopwords.txt" (remove the .example extension)
# 3. Add your custom stopwords or remove built-in ones (see below)
# 4. Rebuild your full-text search index for changes to take effect
#
# Configuration directory locations:
# - Windows: %APPDATA%\GoldenDict\stopwords.txt
# - Linux/Unix: ~/.goldendict/stopwords.txt or ~/.config/goldendict/stopwords.txt
# - macOS: ~/.goldendict/stopwords.txt
# - Portable: <program_directory>/portable/stopwords.txt
#
# Syntax:
# - Lines starting with # are comments
# - Empty lines are ignored
# - Regular words (e.g., "example") will be ADDED to the stopwords list
# - Words prefixed with minus (e.g., "-the") will be REMOVED from built-in stopwords
# - Your custom stopwords will be MERGED with the built-in stopwords
# - Duplicates are automatically removed
#
# IMPORTANT for CJK (Chinese/Japanese/Korean):
# - Only 2-character stopwords are GUARANTEED to work reliably
# - Single CJK characters: effectiveness UNCERTAIN (may only work if isolated)
# - Multi-character phrases (>2): will NOT work (split into bigrams)
# - Recommendation: Use 2-character combinations for best results

# Example 1: Add your domain-specific stopwords
# myterm
# technical_jargon
# acronym

# Example 2: Remove built-in stopwords you want to search
# -the
# -and
# -or
